sentences: Ruth Nye MBE (born 1932) is an Australian pianist and teacher, based in the United Kingdom.
She married fellow Australian Ross Nye in 1956.
Ruth Nye was appointed a Member of the Order of the British Empire (MBE) in the 2007 Queen's Birthday Honours list.
In 2008 a Fellowship of the Royal College of Music was conferred on her by the Prince of Wales.
Ruth Nye is currently on the faculty of the Yehudi Menuhin School in Surrey, UK and the Royal College of Music in London, UK.
